<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-03-17T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-03-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 L 36/154: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-03-17T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 17,
                                        1924—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>37. Our no. 32 of March 10, 4 p.m. and your no. 50 of March 12, 10 p.m.
                            The Department approved your suggestion for short delay in requesting
                                <hi rend="italic">agrément</hi> for Laughlin, but considering time
                            which has passed since the change of Ministry and since events reported
                            in your telegram no. 50, you are now instructed to carry out the
                            instructions given in our telegram no. 32.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>